This paper is about grounding natural language in images, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed model involves compositional reasoning and bottom-up visual reasoning, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions benchmarks, which suggests that it involves experimental evaluation and performance analysis, which is a common theme in information retrieval (cs.IR).
